### Module 02 — hit each strategy and compare

@base = http://localhost:3002

# ---------- CACHE-ASIDE ----------

### Cold read — should be ~200 ms (DB latency)
GET {{base}}/aside/products/1

### Immediately again — should be ~1–5 ms (cache hit)
GET {{base}}/aside/products/1

### Update — cache is INVALIDATED, next read will miss again
PATCH {{base}}/aside/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 149
}

### Read again — cold again (~200 ms)
GET {{base}}/aside/products/1


# ---------- WRITE-THROUGH ----------

### Warm the cache
GET {{base}}/through/products/2

### Update — cache is REWRITTEN in the same request
PATCH {{base}}/through/products/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 25
}

### Read — still fast because write-through kept the cache warm
GET {{base}}/through/products/2


# ---------- WRITE-BEHIND ----------

### Update — should return in a few ms (DB write is deferred)
PATCH {{base}}/behind/products/3
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stock": 999
}

### Read — hits the just-updated cache
GET {{base}}/behind/products/3


# ---------- Peek at cache keys ----------
GET {{base}}/_cache/cache:product:1
GET {{base}}/_cache/cache:product:2
GET {{base}}/_cache/cache:product:3


# ---------- List endpoint (cache-aside, TTL 30s) ----------
GET {{base}}/products
GET {{base}}/products
